<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 3:47PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHEASTERN ROCKINGHAM COUNTY
THROUGH 415 PM EDT...
At 346 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Monroeton, or 9 miles southwest of Reidsville, moving southeast at
25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Reidsville...
Wentworth...
Bethany...
Monroeton...
and Haw River State Park.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
